## 1. Planning Phase

### 1.1 Understand Requirements

- Identify the specific feature or enhancement needed
- Clarify functional and non-functional requirements
- Understand user needs and expected outcomes
- Define the scope of the enhancement

### 1.2 Analyze Existing Code

- Review the current implementation related to the feature
- Identify components that will be affected
- Understand data flow and dependencies
- Identify potential edge cases or constraints

### 1.3 Create Design Plan

- Create a high-level design for the enhancement
- Identify interfaces and interaction patterns
- Document data structures and state management
- Consider error handling approach

### 1.4 Task Breakdown

- Break down the implementation into specific tasks
- Prioritize and sequence tasks
- Identify dependencies between tasks
- Estimate effort for each task

## 2. Creative Phase

### 2.1 Explore Alternatives

- Explore different implementation approaches
- Consider multiple design patterns
- Research existing solutions
- Identify pros and cons of each approach

### 2.2 Evaluate Options

- Evaluate alternatives based on:
  - Maintainability
  - Performance
  - Compatibility with existing system
  - Extensibility
  - Complexity
  - Test coverage

### 2.3 Prototype if Needed

- Create quick prototypes for complex features
- Test challenging aspects of the implementation
- Explore technical risks with proof-of-concepts
- Validate design assumptions

### 2.4 Finalize Approach

- Document the chosen approach
- Outline implementation steps
- Define success criteria
- Update the implementation plan

## 3. Implementation Phase

### 3.1 Environment Setup

- Ensure development environment is ready
- Set up necessary tools and dependencies
- Create a feature branch for the work
- Configure test environment if needed

### 3.2 Create Scaffolding

- Implement basic structure of the feature
- Create new files/classes/methods as needed
- Set up interfaces between components
- Establish error handling patterns

### 3.3 Implement Core Features

- Implement the main functionality
- Follow the AgenticFleet coding standards
- Implement proper error handling
- Add logging as appropriate

### 3.4 Unit Testing

- Write unit tests for the new functionality
- Ensure tests are comprehensive
- Verify edge cases are handled
- Run tests frequently during implementation

### 3.5 Refinement

- Refactor code for clarity and maintainability
- Address any performance considerations
- Ensure proper error handling throughout
- Review for consistency with style guidelines

### 3.6 Integration Testing

- Test the feature in the context of the full system
- Verify interactions with other components
- Check for unintended side effects
- Validate configuration settings

## 4. Reflection Phase

### 4.1 Code Review

- Review your implementation objectively
- Check that code follows project guidelines
- Look for edge cases or potential issues
- Identify any areas for improvement

### 4.2 Verify Requirements

- Confirm all requirements are satisfied
- Check for any missed use cases
- Verify success criteria are met
- Ensure non-functional requirements are addressed

### 4.3 Update Documentation

- Update user documentation if needed
- Add or update technical documentation
- Ensure code is well-commented
- Document any configuration changes

### 4.4 Finalize PR

- Prepare a comprehensive pull request
- Document the changes and implementation approach
- Address any feedback from reviewers
- Finalize the feature implementation

